cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language understanding (NLU) tasks and specifically focuses on the learnability of commonsense knowledge relations represented in CONCEPTNET. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses a neural open world multi-label classification approach, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). The paper also deals with evaluating classification accuracy, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper addresses the challenges of relation ambiguity and argument types, which can be considered as a sub-topic of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
